Aetna Life and Casualty, Hartford, said Robert J. Clark, president of the Commercial Insurance division, had advised the company that he would be resigning because of ''personal reasons.''

* American Express Bank Ltd., the international banking arm of American Express Co., elected Larry F. Clyde executive vice president, financial institutions marketing.

* American Savings Bank appointed Joseph C. La Magna senior vice president and controller.

* Crowley Foods, Paterson, N.J., promoted David P. Coyne to chief operating officer of one of its subsidiaries, A. M. Axelrod & Sons Inc., Binghamton, N.Y.

* Graphic Scanning Corp., Teaneck, N.J., said its chairman and acting chief executive, Stephen M. Greenberg, had resigned to practice law.